  Lect#14      UNIX & C  Spring96
  
There is no way anyone can memorize or know every command & feature of
UNIX system and shell operators & scripts, at least what best can be done
is to familiarize with the basic stuff and then leave special skills to
the future (workplace), like gaining hands- on-experience and
expertise............. 
  
  As for C-shell details and programming I recommend:
  
  "Teach Yourself the UNIX C Shell in 14 days"
  David Ennis & James C. Armstrong, Jr., SAMS Publishing (1994)
  
  Topics of interest:
  
  1. Built-in shell variables:
     - $argv             the argument list
     - $autologout       the auto-logoff timer
     - $cdpath      the directory stack
     - $child       the background process ID
     - $cwd              the current working directory
     - $fignore          the filename completion suffixes
     - $histchars        the history substitution characters
     - $history          the history list size
     - $home        the user's home directory
     - $mail             the user's mail path
     - $path             the directory search list
     - $prompt      the C-shell prompt string
     - $savehist         the size of the saved history
     - $shell            the default shell path
     - $status      the command return status
     - $time             the command timer control;
     - $$           the current process ID
  
  Variables that act as switches:
     - $echo
     - $filec
     - $hardpaths
     - $ignoreeof
     - $nobeep
     - $noclobber
     - $noglob
     - $nonomatch
     - $notify
     - $verbose
  
      
  2. C-shell built-in commands:
     Navigation and directory stack commands:
          - cd and chdir
          - puchd
          - popd
          - dirs
     Shell variable commands:
          - set
          - setenv
          - unset
          - unsetenv
          - @
     Miscellaneous commands:
          - alias and unalias
          - echo
          - history
          - time
          - repeat
          - umask
          - eval
          - source
          - glob
     Shell termination commands:
          - exit
          - exec
          - login
          - logout
          - EOF
     Job Control commands:
          - jobs
          - fg
          - bg
          - The % command
          - notify
          - kill
          - stop
          - suspend
          - The wait command
     Hash Table command:
          - hashstat
          - rehash
          - unhash
     Resource Control commands:
          - limit
          - unlimit
          - nice
          - nohup
  
  3. Programming with C-shell:
     Looping commands:
          - foreach
          - while
          - break
          - continue
          - goto
     Conditional commands:
          - The if command
          - switch
          - case
          - default
          - breaksw
     Interrupt handling command:
          - shift
     
